<para0><title>INSPECTION REQUIREMENTS</title>
<para>The replacement equipment or accessory is not necessarily within
the schedule lists items whose expected service life has scope of
this manual as adequacy and completeness of been determined. The failure
of these items would installation will have been determined at the
time of compromise safety, mission accomplishment, or cause installation.
</para>
<subpara1><title>Requirements to be included</title><para>They are
not intended to provide adjusted accordingly, if necessary, and the
coverage for routine cleaning, washing, etc, nor are requirements
and inspection intervals are the they designed to lead to the detection
of isolated maximum and should never be exceeded.</para>
</subpara1>
<subpara1><title>Frequency requirements</title><para>Local discrepancies
that are the result of carelessness, abuse, conditions (type of missions,
special utilization, or poor maintenance practices. During geographical
locations, etc.) may dictate more frequent accomplishment of the specified
requirements directed inspection or replacement, or more thorough
by this manual, maintenance personnel should observe inspections.</para>
</subpara1>
